    <p><b>The next generation hybrid mobile applications</b> look like original native applications, but they have significant benefits. The development of hybrid mobile applications is similar to <b>web apps development</b>, but is tailored to mobile platforms.</p>
    <p>For users, there is practically no difference between the new hybrid application and the original native. Both types of apps can be downloaded from the App Store or Google Play, both can be stored on a mobile device and started in the same way. Examples of well-known <b>hybrid mobile applications</b> are Instagram, Uber, LinkedIn and Travelocity.</p>
    <p>The major benefit of hybrid applications development is that the same components can be used on different platforms, so developers do not need to repeatedly overwrite applications from scratch for each mobile platform. One app works with minor modifications on Android smartphones, iPhone, tablets and a web browser.</p>

